						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Vishṇumūrti temple.</p>						

						<p>1499 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1421, Siddhārthi, Kārttika-paurṇami,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1499 A.D., October 19.</hi> The details, however, cannot be verified.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of money income and probably also some land to god Kōṭinātha by <hi rend="bold">Basavarasa-voḍeya</hi> who appears to have got the temple repaired, when he was ruling <hi rend="bold">Tuḷu-rājya.</hi> As the record is damaged, the details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
